==Old High German==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*klaini-'', ''klainiz'' ("brilliantly bright", "fine", "elegant"), whence also Old English ''[[clæne]]''.  ''*Klaini-'' from Proto-Indo-European ''*glei-'' ("to stick", "to smudge").
===Adjective===
'''kleini'''
# [[small]], [[fine]], [[slender]]
# [[soft]], [[clean]]
# [[smart]], [[thorough]], [[wise]], [[crafty]], [[keen]]
# [[costly]]


===Etymology===
From Proto-Germanic ''*klainīn-'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*glei-'' ("to stick", "to smudge").
===Noun===
'''kleinī'''

# [[beauty]], [[delicateness]], [[cleanness]]
# [[experience]], [[cleverness]]
# [[proof]], [[knowledge]], [[sense]]

